<extraproject name="Releng/QA Hardware" lead="plasmaroo">
Release Engineering maintains its own set of hardware for development, testing and release-building, as well as the porting of Gentoo Linux to new architectures. Currently, this hardware consists of a dual-CPU 900Mhz zx6000 Itanium 2 system with 4GB of RAM on extended loan from HP, and a dual Opteron AMD64 system built from parts donated by AMD, NVIDIA, The Gentoo Foundation, and Gentoo/AMD64. All systems are running Gentoo Linux.  Access to these machines is requested by contacting <mail link="plasmaroo@gentoo.org">Tim Yamin</mail> and is currently restricted to Release Engineering members.
</extraproject>

